# DataTable

Use `<DataTable>` from `@/components/data-table` for **every** list/table view. Never write raw `<table>` markup.

## Imports

```tsx
import {
  DataTable,
  NameCell,
  StatusBadge,
  DateCell,
  checkboxColumn,
  actionsColumn,
  type DataTableColumn,
  type RowAction,
  TD_DEFAULT,      // 'whitespace-nowrap px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700'
  TH_DEFAULT,      // standard left-aligned th
} from '@/components/data-table';
```

## DataTable Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `columns` | `DataTableColumn<T>[]` | — | Column definitions |
| `data` | `T[]` | — | Row data |
| `rowKey` | `(row: T) => string` | — | Unique key per row |
| `rowClassName` | `(row: T) => string` | `'hover:bg-gray-50'` | Dynamic row classes |
| `emptyMessage` | `string` | `'No items found.'` | Empty state text |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Show loading row |
| `loadingMessage` | `string` | `'Loading...'` | Loading row text |
| `footer` | `ReactNode` | — | After-table content (e.g. `<Pagination>`) |
| `className` | `string` | `'mt-8'` | Outer wrapper classes |

## Column Definition

```tsx
interface DataTableColumn<T> {
  header: ReactNode;
  headerClassName?: string;  // default: TH_DEFAULT
  cell: (row: T) => ReactNode;
  cellClassName?: string;    // default: TD_DEFAULT
}
```

Most columns need no `cellClassName` override — `TD_DEFAULT` handles padding, text size, color, and `whitespace-nowrap`. Only override for special cases (e.g. `NameCell` columns use `'px-6 py-4'` to allow wrapping).

## Reusable Cell Components

### NameCell — linked name + optional subtitle

```tsx
cell: (row) => <NameCell href={`/resources/${row.id}`} name={row.name} subtitle={row.description} />,
cellClassName: 'px-6 py-4',
```

Props: `href`, `name` (string | null), `subtitle?` (string | null), `fallback?` (default `'Untitled'`).
Renders the name as a primary-600 link with a truncated gray subtitle below.

### StatusBadge — consistent status pill

```tsx
cell: (row) => <StatusBadge status={row.deletedAt ? 'deleted' : 'active'} />,
```

Statuses: `'active'` (green), `'inactive'` (gray), `'deleted'` (red).
Optional `label` prop overrides the display text (e.g. `<StatusBadge status="active" label="Configured" />`).

### DateCell — formatted date

```tsx
cell: (row) => <DateCell date={row.createdAt} />,
```

Uses `toLocaleDateString()` — change here to update all tables at once.

## checkboxColumn Factory

For bulk-select tables, call `checkboxColumn()` as the **first** column:

```tsx
checkboxColumn<RowType>({
  selected,            // Set<string>
  onToggle: toggleSelect,
  onToggleAll: toggleAll,
  allSelected,         // boolean
  rowId: (row) => row.id,
  isSelectable: (row) => !row.deletedAt,  // optional guard
}),
```

## actionsColumn Factory

Use `actionsColumn()` as the **last** column. Never write raw action button JSX in column definitions.

Each action is described declaratively with `{ icon, label, onClick }`:

```tsx
actionsColumn<RowType>([
  { icon: 'clone',  label: 'Clone item',  onClick: (row) => handleClone(row.id), loading: (row) => cloningId === row.id },
  { icon: 'edit',   label: 'Edit item',   onClick: (row) => router.push(`/items/${row.id}/edit`) },
  { icon: 'delete', label: 'Delete item',  onClick: (row) => handleDelete(row.id, row.name), variant: 'danger', loading: (row) => deletingId === row.id },
])
```

### RowAction descriptor

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `icon` | `'clone' \| 'delete' \| 'edit'` | Built-in icon |
| `label` | `string` | Tooltip text |
| `onClick` | `(row: T) => void` | Click handler |
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'danger'` | Button style (default: `'default'`) |
| `loading` | `(row: T) => boolean` | Shows spinner when true |
| `hidden` | `(row: T) => boolean` | Hides button when true |

For custom components that don't fit the icon/label/onClick pattern (e.g. `DeployToEnvironmentButton`), use the render escape hatch:

```tsx
{ render: (row) => <DeployToEnvironmentButton strategyId={row.id} variant="icon" /> }
```

### Strategies example (multiple actions)

```tsx
const actions = useMemo<RowAction<StrategyListItem>[]>(() => [
  { icon: 'clone', label: 'Clone strategy', onClick: (s) => handleClone(s.id), loading: (s) => cloningId === s.id },
  { render: (s) => <DeployToEnvironmentButton strategyId={s.id} variant="icon" /> },
  { icon: 'delete', label: 'Delete strategy', onClick: (s) => handleDelete(s.id, s.name), variant: 'danger', loading: (s) => deletingId === s.id },
], [handleClone, handleDelete, cloningId, deletingId]);

// Then in columns:
actionsColumn(actions),
```

### Input presets example (single action, conditional visibility)

```tsx
actionsColumn<InputPresetRow>([
  { icon: 'clone', label: 'Clone preset', onClick: (ip) => handleClone(ip.id), loading: (ip) => cloningId === ip.id, hidden: (ip) => !!ip.deletedAt },
])
```

## Class Name Constants

| Constant | Value | Use for |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `TD_DEFAULT` | `'whitespace-nowrap px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700'` | Most data cells (applied automatically) |
| `TH_DEFAULT` | `'px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-600'` | Most header cells (applied automatically) |

## Rules

- Always define `columns` with `useMemo` to avoid re-renders.
- Use `footer` for `<Pagination>` — keep it inside the card.
- Pass `className=""` when the default `mt-8` spacing is unwanted.
- Prefer cell components (`NameCell`, `StatusBadge`, `DateCell`) over inline JSX.
- Use `actionsColumn()` for all action columns — never write raw action button JSX.
- Only override `cellClassName` when `TD_DEFAULT` doesn't fit (name columns, custom action cells).
